SENATE BILL 957
F1 6lr1938
CF HB 1115
By: Senators Gile and Simonaire
Introduced and read first time: February 8, 2026
Assigned to: Rules
Re–referred to: Education, Energy, and the Environment, February 22, 2026
Committee Report: Favorable with amendments
Senate action: Adopted
Read second time: March 4, 2026
CHAPTER ______
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Education – Career Ladder – National Board Certification Associated Salary
3 Increases
4 FOR the purpose of clarifying that a teacher who holds a certain National Board
5 Certification that was renewed during a certain period of time and has a 10–year
6 award period and is subject to a renewal process is eligible for certain salary
7 increases associated with the career ladder; applying this Act retroactively; and
8 generally relating to National Board Certified teachers and the career ladder.
9 BY repealing and reenacting, without amendments,
10 Article – Education
11 Section 6–1001
12 Annotated Code of Maryland
13 (2025 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
14 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
15 Article – Education
16 Section 6–1009
17 Annotated Code of Maryland
18 (2025 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
19 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
20 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
[Brackets] indicate matter deleted from existing law.
Underlining indicates amendments to bill.
Strike out indicates matter stricken from the bill by amendment or deleted from the law by
amendment. *sb0957*

2 SENATE BILL 957
1 Article – Education
2 6–1001.
3 (a) In this subtitle the following words have the meanings indicated.
4 (b) “Career ladder” means the career ladder for public prekindergarten, primary,
5 or secondary school teachers in the State implemented by county boards that meets the
6 standards set forth under this subtitle and the standards adopted by the Department.
7 (c) “NBC” means National Board Certification issued by the National Board for
8 Professional Teaching Standards.
9 (d) “NBC teacher” means a teacher who holds an active National Board
10 Certification.
11 (e) (1) “Teacher” means a certified public school employee who is primarily
12 responsible and accountable for teaching the students in the class.
13 (2) “Teacher” does not include, unless otherwise provided:
14 (i) Curriculum specialists;
15 (ii) Instructional aides;
16 (iii) Attendance personnel;
17 (iv) Psychologists;
18 (v) Social workers;
19 (vi) Clerical personnel;
20 (vii) An individual with a Resident Teacher Certificate; or
21 (viii) An individual with a certification for career professionals.
22 6–1009.
23 (a) (1) Subject to paragraph (2) of this subsection, beginning on July 1, 2022,
24 teacher salary increases associated with the career ladder shall at a minimum include the
25 following:
26 (i) Becoming an NBC teacher – $10,000 salary increase;
27 (ii) An NBC teacher teaching at a low–performing school as
28 identified by the county board – $7,000 salary increase;

SENATE BILL 957 3
1 (iii) Becoming lead teacher – $5,000 salary increase;
2 (iv) Becoming distinguished teacher – $10,000 salary increase;
3 (v) Becoming professor distinguished teacher – $15,000 salary
4 increase; and
5 (vi) Becoming a distinguished principal – $15,000 salary increase.
6 (2) The teacher salary increases under paragraph (1) of this subsection do
7 not apply to paragraph (1)(iii) through (vi) of this subsection until § 6–1002(a) of this
8 subtitle becomes effective as recommended by the Department and approved by the
9 Accountability and Implementation Board.
10 (b) (1) IN THIS SUBSECTION, “10–YEAR NBC” MEANS AN NBC AWARDED
11 TO A TEACHER ON OR BEFORE DECEMBER 31, 2021, THAT:
12 (I) HAS AN EXPIRATION DATE WAS RENEWED BETWEEN
13 JANUARY 1, 2016, AND DECEMBER 31, 2031 2021, INCLUSIVE; AND
14 (II) HAS A 10–YEAR AWARD PERIOD;
15 (III) WAS SUBJECT TO THE RENEWAL PROCESS FOR RETENTION
16 OF CERTIFICATION; AND
17 (IV) PROHIBITS THE HOLDER FROM USING THE MAINTENANCE
18 OF CERTIFICATION PROCESS FOR RETENTION OF CERTIFICATION UNTIL THE
19 10–YEAR AWARD PERIOD HAS EXPIRED.
20 (2) Salary increases associated with maintenance of an NBC OR RENEWAL
21 OF A 10–YEAR NBC are subject to collective bargaining in accordance with § 6–408 of this
22 title.
23 [(2)] (3) The State share for the following salary increases provided under
24 paragraph [(1)] (2) of this subsection shall not exceed the following amounts:
25 (i) FOR AN NBC THAT HAS A 5–YEAR AWARD PERIOD EXCEPT
26 AS PROVIDED IN ITEM (II) OF THIS PARAGRAPH:
27 1. Earning a first maintenance of NBC – $8,000 salary
28 increase;
29 [(ii)] 2. Earning a second maintenance of NBC – $7,000 salary
30 increase; and

4 SENATE BILL 957
1 [(iii)] 3. Earning a third maintenance of NBC – $6,000 salary
2 increase; AND
3 (II) FOR A 10–YEAR NBC:
4 1. EARNED 5 YEARS AFTER EARNING RENEWAL OF A
5 10–YEAR NBC (FIRST MAINTENANCE OF NBC) – $8,000 SALARY INCREASE;
6 2. EARNING A FIRST MAINTENANCE OF A 10–YEAR NBC
7 AFTER 5 YEARS FROM THE DATE OF RENEWAL MAINTENANCE OF CERTIFICATION
8 THAT BEGINS A 5–YEAR AWARD PERIOD (SECOND MAINTENANCE OF NBC) – $7,000
9 SALARY INCREASE; AND
10 3. EARNING A SECOND MAINTENANCE OF A 10–YEAR
11 NBC MAINTENANCE OF CERTIFICATION (THIRD MAINTENANCE OF NBC) – $6,000
12 SALARY INCREASE.
13 (c) (1) If a teacher is eligible for more than one salary increase under
14 subsections (a) and (b) of this section, the teacher shall receive all salary increases that
15 apply.
16 (2) A teacher that receives a salary increase under subsection (a)(2) of this
17 section for teaching at a low–performing school may not lose that salary increase while
18 teaching at the school even if the school ceases to be low–performing.
19 (d) On or before July 1, 2024, each county shall demonstrate to the Accountability
20 and Implementation Board established under § 5–402 of this article that, during the period
21 between July 1, 2019, and June 30, 2024, teachers in the county received a 10% salary
22 increase above the negotiated schedule of salary increases between the public school
23 employer and exclusive representative for the employee organization.
24 (e) Beginning on July 1, 2026, the minimum teacher salary for all teachers shall
25 be $60,000.
26 (f) (1) In this subsection, “total program amount” means the sum of, for each
27 item under subsections (a) and [(b)(2)] (B)(3) of this section:
28 (i) The teacher salary increase multiplied by the number of teachers
29 receiving the salary increase; and
30 (ii) Rounded to the nearest whole dollar.

SENATE BILL 957 5
1 (2) The increase in the salary required under subsections (a) and [(b)(2)]
2 (B)(3) of this section shall be a shared cost between the State and the county in accordance
3 with this subsection.
4 (3) The required State share for each county is the result of the following
5 calculation multiplied by 0.5 and rounded to the nearest whole dollar:
6 (i) The salary increase multiplied by the number of teachers eligible
7 to receive the salary increase in the prior fiscal year;
8 (ii) Divide the result calculated under item (i) of this paragraph by
9 the ratio, rounded to seven decimal places, of local wealth per pupil to statewide wealth per
10 pupil as defined in § 5–201 of this article; and
11 (iii) Multiply the result calculated under item (ii) of this paragraph
12 by the result, rounded to seven decimal places, that results from dividing the total program
13 amount by the sum of all of the results calculated under item (ii) of this paragraph for all
14 counties.
15 (4) The required local share is equal to the total program amount for each
16 county minus the State share calculated under paragraph (3) of this subsection and
17 rounded to the nearest whole dollar.
18 (g) (1) Beginning in fiscal year 2023, the State shall distribute the State share
19 of the teacher salary increases as calculated under subsection (f) of this section to each
20 county board.
21 (2) Beginning in fiscal year 2023, the county shall distribute the local share
22 of the teacher salary increases as calculated under subsection (f) of this section to each
23 county board.
24 (3) Beginning in fiscal year 2023, the county board shall distribute the
25 State and the local share of the teacher salary increase to the school in which the teacher
26 works.
27 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall be construed to
28 apply retroactively and shall be applied to and interpreted to affect any teacher salary
29 increases associated with the career ladder for teachers holding a National Board
30 Certificate under § 6–1009 of the Education Article on or before July 1, 2026.
31 SECTION 3. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
32 1, 2026.

